    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "How long does MRI screening take?  ",
        "answer": "It usually takes between 20 and 60 minutes depending on the type of scan.  \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is MRI screening painful?  ",
        "answer": "No, the scan is painless. You will only need to stay still during the procedure."
      },
      {
        "question": "When will I receive my results?  ",
        "answer": "Cadabams provides fast turnaround, often delivering results on the same day.  \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does an MRI screening typically cost?",
        "answer": "The MRI screening cost can vary significantly based on the extent of the scan (e.g., full body vs. specific region), the facility, and geographic location. As it's often an elective procedure for asymptomatic individuals, it may not always be covered by insurance. Cadabams Diagnostics can provide you with specific pricing for our MRI Screening packages. We recommend you contact us directly for the latest information on MRI screening cost. "
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before MRI screening?  ",
        "answer": "Yes, unless you have been instructed to fast for contrast-based scans.  \n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Does insurance cover MRI screening?  ",
        "answer": "Coverage varies depending on policy. It is best to confirm with your insurer.  \n"
      }
    ],
